                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13926.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Canada</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Vera Cruz</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-11-29T10:00:00-06:36">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 29, 1914, 10 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The following has been received from the Foreign Office here: <quote
                        rend="blockquote">
                        <p>I have the honor to inform you that, due to war necessities, the First
                            Chief of the Constitutionalist Army has issued a decree ordering the
                            Government offices to be transferred to such places as circumstances may
                            dictate, the National Government remaining for the present at this
                            port.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canada</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
